# Files consumed on the Linux Raspberry Pi must keep LF line endings regardless of the committer's
# platform — a CRLF in a shebang breaks the script (`/usr/bin/env bash\r: No such file or directory`),
# and systemd is equally unforgiving of CRLF in unit files.
*.sh      text eol=lf
*.service text eol=lf
*.timer   text eol=lf
